### General 

- Access is denied by default and is only allowed once a policy was applied to a resource.
- Policies can be attached to a rouse and resources to control access 
- A role can be assumed by a service such as EC2 or lambda
- You can attach a policy to a role. Note that permissions as set in the policy.
- AWS managed policies covers broader scope, whereas customer managed policies are specific and narrowed.
